		"description": {
			"value": "<p><em>Wondrous Item - Uncommon (Requires Attunement)</em></p><p><em>A magic item like this counts as magical for overcoming effects.</em></p><p><strong>Activation</strong> - 3 Charges ([[/r 1d3]]/Dawn)</p><ul><li><p><strong>Action</strong> (1 -3 Charges): While these pipes are on your person, ordinary rats and giant rats are Indifferent unless you threaten or harm them. Playing the pipes and expending 1–3 charges calls one @UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-summoned-creatures.Actor.aC092PbaBHtbIB2D]{Swarm of Rats} per charge if enough rats are within half a mile (charge is wasted if not). Called swarms move toward the music by the shortest route but aren’t controlled. Any uncontrolled Swarm within 30 feet while you play makes a [[/save WIS 15]]{Wisdom Save (DC 15)}; on a failed save it becomes Friendly and obeys your commands while you keep playing each round (no command = defends itself). If it succeeds or ends a turn more than 30 feet away, it behaves normally and can’t be swayed for 24 hours. Outdoors above ground, the pipes have no effect.</p></li></ul>",
